  "task": "Implement distributed consensus-based JSON-LD SeVoNode storage with strict latency SLAs, atomic multi-node transactions, and Byzantine-resilient garbage collection. Must satisfy all v5 requirements plus: (1) Raft-like distributed consensus — maintain 3-replica quorum across simulated network conditions, reject writes without quorum, recover from partitions using quorum rules; (2) Atomic transactions — multi-node writes must be all-or-nothing with rollback on any failure, transaction log must be immutable, in-flight transactions must survive crashes; (3) Latency SLAs — writes must complete in <150ms (replication + fsync), reads in <20ms (in-memory or cache), violations cause -0.05 fitness penalty per violation; (4) Garbage collection — implement mark-and-sweep across active node references (causal graph + vector clocks), prove no node is deleted while still referenced, handle concurrent mutations during sweep; (5) Digital signatures — every node must be signed with Ed25519, signature verification on read must succeed, detect tampering, support key rotation without breaking old signatures; (6) Partition recovery — detect network splits, implement quorum-based fencing, safely recover without divergent replicas, prove linearizability of all ops post-recovery.",
